 \"from\": 2480, \"to\": 2492}, {\"ngram\": \"John\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2497}, {\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 2528, \"to\": 2542}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Put bluntly, they did it because they hate Jesus Christ and Christianity, which they consider their most dangerous enemy.\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2596, \"end\": 2608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.112379267844763e-14, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2613, \"end\": 2625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999973119884, \"rank\": 2.6862075221911933e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their most dangerous enemy\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are quite open about this now.\\\"\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2711, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That blasphemous display represented a naked expression of the power they now hold over Western culture.\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2801, \"end\": 2816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_culture\", \"score\": 0.999997199460551, \"rank\": 2.8005471393430425e-06, \"text\": \"Western culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_culture\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_culture\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That blasphemous display\", \"from\": 2713, \"to\": 2737}, {\"ngram\": \"a naked expression\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2768}, {\"ngram\": \"the power\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2781}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They know they can mock the very cornerstone of our entire civilization in front of an audience of tens of millions and they will receive applause for doing so.\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2978, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the very cornerstone\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 2862}, {\"ngram\": \"our entire civilization\", \"from\": 2866, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 2893, \"to\": 2898}, {\"ngram\": \"an audience\", \"from\": 2902, \"to\": 2913}, {\"ngram\": \"tens\", \"from\": 2917, \"to\": 2921}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 2933}, {\"ngram\": \"applause\", \"from\": 2956, \"to\": 2964}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The best thequeerParis Olympics 'artistic director' and sex performers could come up with is badly deforming others' artistic triumphs.\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 3116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The best thequeerParis Olympics 'artistic director\", \"from\": 2981, \"to\": 3031}, {\"ngram\": \"sex performers\", \"from\": 3037, \"to\": 3051}, {\"ngram\": \"others' artistic triumphs\", \"from\": 3090, \"to\": 3115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They did not think up their own world, symbols, and referents, they just sabotaged others' then pretended what any three-year-old can do is brilliant,\\\" my colleague Joy Pullmannwrote.\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3282, \"end\": 3285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.241992391737515e-36, \"text\": \"Joy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Joy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their own world\", \"from\": 3139, \"to\": 3154}, {\"ngram\": \"symbols\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \"referents\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3178}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 3200, \"to\": 3206}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They can not do anything but mock and deface and corrupt that which is sacred, meaningful, and beautiful.\", \"from\": 3302, \"to\": 3407, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 3318, \"to\": 3326}, {\"ngram\": \"deface\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3346}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are utterly incapable of creating anything of worth because of their own twisted and unnatural view of the world.\", \"from\": 3408, \"to\": 3526, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3455}, {\"ngram\": \"their own twisted and unnatural view\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3512}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3525}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So in their self-loathing they have to tear everything else down in order to free themselves from reality and morality.\", \"from\": 3527, \"to\": 3646, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their self-loathing\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3552}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3581}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3600}, {\"ngram\": \"reality\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3632}, {\"ngram\": \"morality\", \"from\": 3637, \"to\": 3645}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one of its videos of a segment depicting the French Revolution (complete with a decapitated Marie Antoinette), NBC Sportsdescribedthe ceremony as celebrating \\\"liberation.\\\"\", \"from\": 3648, \"to\": 3822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3743, \"end\": 3759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6317419864649603e-42, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its videos\", \"from\": 3658, \"to\": 3668}, {\"ngram\": \"a segment\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3681}, {\"ngram\": \"the French Revolution\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3713}, {\"ngram\": \"liberation\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3820}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To these people, \\\"liberation\\\" does not mean the overthrow of a tyrannical monarch or the creation of a free civil society, even though they constantly frame their own struggle in those terms.\", \"from\": 3824, \"to\": 4015, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these people\", \"from\": 3827, \"to\": 3839}, {\"ngram\": \", \\\"liberation\", \"from\": 3839, \"to\": 3852}, {\"ngram\": \"the overthrow\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3881}, {\"ngram\": \"a tyrannical monarch\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3905}, {\"ngram\": \"the creation\", \"from\": 3909, \"to\": 3921}, {\"ngram\": \"a free civil society\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 3945}, {\"ngram\": \"their own struggle\", \"from\": 3981, \"to\": 3999}, {\"ngram\": \"those terms\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4014}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Liberation\\\" means a state of total exemption from societal norms and a license to indulge in any and all sexual whims - aka, narcissism in its most decadent form.\", \"from\": 4016, \"to\": 4179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Liberation\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4027}, {\"ngram\": \"a state\", \"from\": 4035, \"to\": 4042}, {\"ngram\": \"total exemption\", \"from\": 4046, \"to\": 4061}, {\"ngram\": \"societal norms\", \"from\": 4067, \"to\": 4081}, {\"ngram\": \"a license\", \"from\": 4086, \"to\": 4095}, {\"ngram\": \"any and all sexual whims\", \"from\": 4110, \"to\": 4134}, {\"ngram\": \"narcissism\", \"from\": 4142, \"to\": 4152}, {\"ngram\": \"its most decadent form\", \"from\": 4156, \"to\": 4178}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have no qualms about destroying or desecrating civilization if it achieves their radical sexual freedom.\", \"from\": 4180, \"to\": 4289, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no qualms\", \"from\": 4190, \"to\": 4199}, {\"ngram\": \"civilization\", \"from\": 4232, \"to\": 4244}, {\"ngram\": \"their radical sexual freedom\", \"from\": 4260, \"to\": 4288}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In fact, for many it has become akin to a fetish.\", \"from\": 4290, \"to\": 4339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fact\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4297}, {\"ngram\": \"a fetish\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"God, tradition, history, and even the concept of civil society place restrictions and expectations on their behavior, and they can not stand it.\", \"from\": 4341, \"to\": 4485, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 4341, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"tradition\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4355}, {\"ngram\": \"history\", \"from\": 4357, \"to\": 4364}, {\"ngram\": \"even the concept\", \"from\": 4370, \"to\": 4386}, {\"ngram\": \"civil society place restrictions\", \"from\": 4390, \"to\": 4422}, {\"ngram\": \"expectations\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4439}, {\"ngram\": \"their behavior\", \"from\": 4443, \"to\": 4457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They share the same vision as a long line of French thinkers from Rousseau to Foucault - a blinding hatred for what they consider \\\"inequality\\\" but what the rest of us see as the pillars of a functioning civilization.\", \"from\": 4486, \"to\": 4702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4531, \"end\": 4537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999965665283352, \"rank\": 3.4237030111951805e-06, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4552, \"end\": 4560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Jacques_Rousseau\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.825300160449082e-44, \"text\": \"Rousseau\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4964182\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Jacques_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Jacques_Rousseau\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same vision\", \"from\": 4497, \"to\": 4512}, {\"ngram\": \"a long line\", \"from\": 4516, \"to\": 4527}, {\"ngram\": \"Foucault\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4572}, {\"ngram\": \"a blin